                                                                                                                                                                                                       Since 1st March, 1999                                                               Malaysias influential former Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad quit the ruling party today after a long feud with his successor, deepening the cracks that appeared after the partys recent massive electoral losses.                 Sri Lankan military attacked rebel positions in the islands far north yesterday, amid daily land, air and sea raids, killing 61 Tamil Tigers, the military said today.                   The hills are alive... with the sound of protest.                   Bangladeshs army-backed interim government has approved a new counter-terrorism law, laying down a maximum penalty of death for anyone involved in terrorist activities                                   Mahathir Mohamad
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
